<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="744" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/197.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Charles A. Conant</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: I have examined the copies of the
                            proposed contracts between the bankers and the fiscal agent of the
                            Government of Honduras which are enclosed herewith,<note n="1" xml:id="d744fn1">Not printed.</note> with a view to the changes made
                            since my letter to the Department of February 6th last.</p>
                        <p>I do not find in the changes made any reason to modify the opinions
                            expressed in that letter. The changes appear to be of a nature to add to
                            the protection afforded to the Government of Honduras under the
                            contract, and to give greater clearness to certain minor provisions.</p>
                        <p>Yours very respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles A. Conant.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>